@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Server.ProtectedBrowserStorage
@using MyCheeseShop.Model
@inject ProtectedSessionStorage ProtectedSessionStore
@inject ShoppingCart ShoppingCart

<div class="card mb-3 border-primary" style="max-width: 1200px;">
    <div class="row g-0">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <img src="/img/cheeses/@Cheese.ImageUrl" class="img-fluid rounded-start">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-8">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title" style="font-size:50px">@Cheese.Name</h5>
                <h5><p class="card-text" style="font-size:25px">@Cheese.Description</p></h5>
                <h5><span class="badge text-bg-primary" style="font-size:25px">TYPE: @Cheese.Type</span>
                    <span class="badge text-bg-primary" style="font-size:25px">STRENGTH: @Cheese.Strength</span></h5>
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-12 mt-lg-0 mt-1">
                    <h3><InputSelect class="form-select w-100" @bind-Value="quantity" required>
                    @for (var i = 1; i <= 5; i++)
                    {
                        <option value="@i">@(i * 100)g</option>
                    }
                </InputSelect>
                </h3>
                    <h3><button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="AddToCart">Buy cheese</button></h3>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@code {

    [Parameter]
    public Cheese Cheese { get; set; }

    private int quantity = 1;

    public async Task AddToCart()
    {
        ShoppingCart.AddItem(Cheese, quantity);
        await ProtectedSessionStore.SetAsync("cart", ShoppingCart.GetItems());
    }
}

<EditForm Model="quantity" OnSubmit="AddToCart">
    <div class="row"></div>
</EditForm>